    <section id="id1168789509117">
      <title>The main biomes (Vegetation regions)</title>
      <list id="id1168796874430" list-type="enumerated" number-style="arabic">
        <item>The 5 main biomes</item>
      </list>
      <list id="id1168798132887" list-type="bulleted">
        <item>Vegetation across the world is divided into <emphasis effect="bold">five large biomes</emphasis>:</item>
      </list>
      <list id="id1168789245725" list-type="enumerated" number-style="arabic">
        <item>The Forest Biome</item>
      </list>
      <list id="id1168794306891" list-type="bulleted">
        <item>Tropical forests</item>
        <item>Temperate forests</item>
        <item>Deciduous forests</item>
        <item>Needle leaf forests</item>
        <item>Mediterranean forests (Sclerophyll bush)</item>
        <item>Savannah Biome</item>
        <item>Grasslands Biome</item>
        <item>Desert Biome</item>
        <item>Tundra and ice fields Biome</item>
      </list>
      <para id="id1168789670217">Remember this!</para>
      <para id="id1168794719297"> Human beings have altered or destroyed the original environment of many parts of the world.</para>
      <para id="id1168786840229">2. Area division of the different biomes</para>
